sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant Browser
    participant Django as Django (web)
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    participant McpServer as MCP Server (fastmcp)
    participant ProviderAPI as Provider API (Anthropic or Llama)

    Note over User,DB: Add or replace an API key

    User->>Browser: Navigate to /settings/api-keys/
    Browser->>Django: GET /settings/api-keys/
    Django->>DB: SELECT UserApiKey WHERE user=request.user
    Django-->>Browser: Render key list with masked suffixes only

    User->>Browser: Click Add key or Edit
    Browser->>Django: GET /settings/api-keys/form/ [HTMX]
    Django-->>Browser: Render inline form partial

    User->>Browser: Select provider, enter label and key value
    Browser->>Django: POST /settings/api-keys/ with provider, label, key_value, base_url
    Django->>Django: Fernet.encrypt(key_value) using FIELD_ENCRYPTION_KEY
    Django->>DB: INSERT or UPDATE UserApiKey with encrypted_key and masked_suffix
    Note over Django: masked_suffix = last 4 chars of key_value stored in plaintext for display
    Django-->>Browser: HTMX swap: updated key list partial, form closed
    Browser-->>User: Key list shows new row with masked suffix e.g. ****3f8a

    Note over User,DB: Dashboard load — check key status

    User->>Browser: Navigate to /dashboard/
    Browser->>Django: GET /dashboard/
    Django->>DB: SELECT UserApiKey WHERE user=request.user AND is_active=true
    alt No active key found
        Django-->>Browser: Render chat panel in no-key state with link to /settings/api-keys/
        Browser-->>User: Yellow warning panel: No API key configured
    else Active key found
        Django-->>Browser: Render chat panel enabled with provider name and masked suffix in header
        Browser-->>User: Chat input active, token indicator visible
    end

    Note over User,ProviderAPI: Chat dispatch using user key

    User->>Browser: Send chat message
    Browser->>Django: HTMX POST /dashboard/chat/ with message
    Django->>DB: SELECT UserApiKey WHERE user=request.user AND is_active=true
    alt No active key
        Django-->>Browser: SSE error: no_api_key
        Browser-->>User: Chat panel reverts to no-key state
    else Key found
        Django->>Django: Fernet.decrypt(encrypted_key) in memory only\nKey never written to log or forwarded as plaintext over network
        Django->>McpServer: Forward message and decrypted key and base_url via Docker internal network
        Note over Django,McpServer: Key passed in request header, not in body\nMCP server uses it for one call then discards it
        McpServer->>ProviderAPI: API call with user-supplied key
        alt Auth error from provider
            ProviderAPI-->>McpServer: 401 Unauthorized
            McpServer-->>Django: auth_error event
            Django-->>Browser: SSE error: api_key_rejected
            Browser-->>User: Chat panel shows: API key rejected — check or replace in Settings\nToken budget is not decremented
        else Success
            ProviderAPI-->>McpServer: Response with token usage
            McpServer-->>Django: SSE stream with response and token_delta
            Django->>DB: McpSession.tokens_used += token_delta
            Django-->>Browser: SSE stream with text and updated token counts
            Browser-->>User: AI response shown, token indicator updated
        end
    end

    Note over User,DB: Delete a key

    User->>Browser: Click Delete on a key row
    Browser->>Django: POST /settings/api-keys/id/delete/ [HTMX]
    Django->>DB: SELECT McpSession WHERE user_api_key_id=id AND ended_at IS NULL
    opt Active session uses this key
        Django->>DB: McpSession.ended_at = now()
    end
    Django->>DB: DELETE UserApiKey WHERE id=id AND user=request.user
    Django-->>Browser: HTMX swap: updated key list with row removed
    Browser-->>User: Key removed; if dashboard chat was open it refreshes to no-key state
